text: This guy is cruising through the East Village blasting "Careless Whisper" and it's like he's leaving a wake of devastating sexiness behind.
My liberal friend is convinced Palin is going to kill in the debate; My conservative friend is convinced she's going to *get* killed. Hmm.
If it's heaping praise on @heather day, get in line behind me.
No, no, I don't have rage issues. But I'm working on developing them!
The financial press failed us as completely this year as journalists did in the run-up to the Iraq war -- where were they?
@torrez @jkottke Happy Birthdays!

This financial crisis is the first time I've tried the classic American stress-reducer: Rank ignorance and deliberate distraction. It works!
Trying to explain to a cabbie that long, slow sweeping circles may not be the most efficient path around Manhattan.
Just got my copy of the I Can Has Cheezburger book, and very appreciative of the shoutout to me in the acknowledgements!
Has anybody done an article on which political parties the CEOs of all these failed (or not) megacorps support? There's a story there.
This is probably one of the best Prince songs that features the use of talk box, Kim Basinger, a sax solo, and a dialogue about a window.
I like that this Friday's presidential debate has the potential to degenerate into history's highest-stakes game of Playing the Dozens.

Tired from a good, productive day. Sorry I couldn't join my 6A peeps, but glad we got to hang out a little!
Getting ready to keynote BlogWorld in a little while. If you're in Vegas, stop by. If not, wish me luck!
I keep seeing Michael from The Wire in all these 90210 billboards around town. I assume he's on the show to murder Bryan Austin Green?
Dear everyone: Please do not take it personally if I stab you in the face. It's just my way of dealing with stress! [[Hugs]]

one-inch inseams threatening.

Dressed up and looking sharp, went to a great restaurant with good friends. Being grown up beats the *hell* out of being young and broke.
A little quick math reveals I'd have to run about 35 miles to work off the calories I ate today. So I'll get right on that then. Tomorrow.
Thanks for the birthday wishes, everybody! It is a good day to be a little older.
